        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 7:31PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 731 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Richford, or 7 miles southwest of Marathon, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hunts Corners, Chenango Valley State Park, Center Lisle, Chenango
Forks, Harford, Newark Valley, West Newark, Lapeer, East Berkshire,
and Willet.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
